00,"euEtsDetails":null}]},"remarkList":[{"modifiedDate":"2022-01-15T00:12:36.217","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"\u2022\tPre-calc:               $22,410 x 21.2 days = $199,367\n\n\u2022\tEarnings:              $24,001 x 29.0 days = $319,033\nDifference:    Originally generated as a 1:1 (Houston-San Jose), charterers declared Acajutla as an additional disport which added $50k in LS freight.  Also, due to a tight delivery window our Panama Canal transit was won via the auction process.  Terms were 50/50 on prebook cost, but since our charterers booked via auction, they assumed the full cost.  As a result we saved approx. $29k in port costs at the canal.  We saw 10 additional in port days of which 8.7 were claimed as demurrage at 19,500/day.  Despite the voyage being extended, $9k was saved in bunkers with an avg of -2mt/day on her ballast \u0026 laden passages.  In port consumption was estimated to be lsmgo for all ports, however in San Jose \u0026 Acajutla she burned vlsfo which further contributed to bunker savings.\nImprovements:  No improvements, but important to note we had off-spec vlsfo stemmed while in Houston.  None of the off-spec parcel was burned as enough ROB was available to reach Balboa after completion of the voyage.  Due to great communication, cooperation, and professionalism between all parties; the suppliers (Peninsula) agreed to cover all de-bunkering and re-supplying costs.\n\nFIXTURE NOTE:\nLargo Sun came open in what was supposed to be a firm market as her dates put her in the middle of the thanksgiving fixing rush. However as we have seen, it didn\u2019t really materialize and we were able to lock in this voyage on her dates to WCCAM with Koch once again right before the market dropped further.   \n\nVessel\tLargo Sun\nVoy#\t2108\nFix#\tKoch usg-wccam\nC/P Date\tNov 24, 2021\nCharterer\tKOCH\nBroker\tAFFINITY\nStart\tBahia Las Minas\nLoad\tHouston\nDischarge\tSan Jose (Guat)\nCargo\t38,000 mt CPP\nLay/Can\tNov 25-26, 2021 (00:00-16:00)\nRate\t$1,025,000\nComm\tCharterer: 2.5%, Broker: 1.25%, Agent: 2%\nTCE\nPNL\t$22,410.27 for 21.2 days\n$199,367 Bss 13kpd\nDemurrage\t$18,500.00"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-01-14T22:09:28.887","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"Chrt Request Speed Up: HOU - P. Canal - Acajutla - consumption better than anticipated - no difference vs theoretical"},{"modifiedDate":"2021-12-11T23:18:48.003","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"Panama Canal port cost at 180k estimated as charterers secured auction spot - CP states only 50/50 split on prebook.  No mention of cost splitting for auction."},{"modifiedDate":"2021-12-02T05:14:39.547","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"TCE dropped due to addition ports added"},{"modifiedDate":"2021-11-24T17:20:21.977","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"TCE improved due to days at Houston updated"}],"offhireList":[],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}